{"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Spooktacular runs macOS virtual machines on Apple Silicon using","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Apple’s Virtualization framework. You interact with it through the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"GUI app or the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook"},{"type":"text","text":" CLI — both backed by the same"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" library. A Kubernetes operator is planned for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a future release."}]},{"type":"aside","name":"Important","style":"important","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You need an Apple Silicon Mac (M1 or later) running","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"macOS 14.0 (Sonoma) or later. Each VM requires at least 20 GB of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"free disk space and 4 CPU cores (see","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/VirtualMachineSpecification\/minimumCPUCount"},{"text":").","type":"text"}]}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Creating a VM with the CLI","level":3,"anchor":"Creating-a-VM-with-the-CLI"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Install Spooktacular and create a VM from the latest compatible IPSW:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"bash","type":"codeListing","code":["# Install via Homebrew","brew install --cask spooktacular","","# Create from the latest compatible IPSW","spook create my-vm --from-ipsw latest","","# Or specify custom hardware resources","spook create runner --cpu 8 --memory 16 --disk 100"]},{"style":"note","type":"aside","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"IPSW installation takes 10–20 minutes per VM. For faster"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"deployment, create a base VM once, then use "},{"code":"spook clone","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"instant copies."}]}]},{"text":"Creating a VM with the GUI","anchor":"Creating-a-VM-with-the-GUI","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Open Spooktacular."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Click the ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"+"}]},{"text":" button or press ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Cmd+N","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Enter a name and adjust hardware settings.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Click "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The app downloads the latest compatible macOS IPSW and installs it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"into a new VM bundle.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Managing VMs","level":3,"anchor":"Managing-VMs"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use the "},{"code":"spook","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" CLI for day-to-day VM management:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["# List all VMs","spook list","","# Start a VM (opens display window)","spook start my-vm","","# Start headless (for CI runners and servers)","spook start my-vm --headless","","# Clone instantly using APFS copy-on-write","spook clone my-vm runner-01","","# Show VM configuration","spook get my-vm","","# Delete a VM permanently","spook delete my-vm --force"],"syntax":"bash"},{"name":"Important","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Apple Silicon supports a maximum of 2 concurrent VMs","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"per host. Attempting to start a third VM fails. See","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/CapacityCheck"},{"text":" for details.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"important"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Provisioning-with-User-Data-Scripts","text":"Provisioning with User-Data Scripts"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Automate VM setup by running a shell script after boot via SSH:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"bash","code":["spook start runner --headless \\","    --user-data ~\/setup.sh \\","    --provision ssh \\","    --ssh-user admin"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ssh"},{"text":" mode waits for the VM to boot, discovers its IP, connects","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"via SSH, and executes your script with real-time output streaming.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Disk-inject provisioning (zero-touch, no SSH required) is in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"progress. See "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/ProvisioningMode","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" for provisioning strategies and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"doc:Provisioning"},{"type":"text","text":" for detailed guidance."}]},{"text":"EC2 Mac Setup","anchor":"EC2-Mac-Setup","type":"heading","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Deploy Spooktacular on AWS EC2 Mac instances to double your CI"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"capacity. Install Spooktacular, create VMs from IPSW, clone"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"configured bases, and start runners with SSH provisioning."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment"},{"type":"text","text":" for detailed EC2 Mac configuration."}]},{"style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A Kubernetes operator (MacOSVM CRD) is planned for a future"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"release. See "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide"},{"type":"text","text":" for the planned architecture."}]}],"type":"aside"}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BlueBubblesGuide"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/MLWorkloads"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/Versioning"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BlueBubblesGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/MLWorkloads","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GettingStarte